{
  "stem": "19690.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 202.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And then they stood up with their arms drawn because by then, the Italians heard what was going on, the dogs were raising Cain.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And they-- the Swiss said to the Italians, don't do anything, they're on Swiss soil.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We were safe.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "We were taken to a guard shack, where a woman made us some hot chocolate and dried our clothes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Then the bus came and picked us up and we were taken to an assembly point in Geneva, which was a school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And there we were interviewed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And we had been told before we left France that if anybody asked, we were to say there was a man with glasses and a beard who brought us and that we did not know his name because no one should know that it was a woman because they knew information went back and forth between the Swiss and the Germans.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Also, we were told we are not to say anything about having any relatives, friends, anybody in France because if they knew we had somebody in France, they would send us back.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And so we were interviewed two or three times over the next two or three days.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Then after about a week, we would put on a train, some of us, and taken to a home for children in Ascona, Switzerland, which was run by a lady by the name of Lily [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "She was a child psychologist who when the unrest started opened this home for children in Ascona.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And there were probably about 40 of us there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Then I found out there was another home that she had another 20.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And she take-- took care of us there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "We had school.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
